cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on the problem of object recognition and classification in computer vision, specifically using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes computational models to improve the generalization capacity of CNNs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the limitations of deep learning models and proposes solutions, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to analyze the results, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
